Heartbroken: Ms Kennedy speaking before the funeral of her best friend and sister-in-law, Mary Richardson Kennedy, in Bedford, New York in May

Ms Kennedy, 52, drove off the highway after the crash, in which her car was damaged and she sustained a flat tire.

Police arrived at the scene after a 911 call reported erratic driving on the freeway.

They then discovered Ms Kennedy passed out at the wheel of the white 2008 Lexus RS 350, according to NBC New York. There were no passengers.

She apparently told police that she had taken prescription sleeping pills - said to include the drug Ambien - before the accident.

After her arrest, Ms Kennedy was charged with driving while impaired with drugs.

